{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":310,"text":"Let's begin with a story."},{"time":4326,"text":"Once upon a time --"},{"time":6277,"text":"well actually less than two years ago --"},{"time":9343,"text":"in a kingdom not so very far away,"},{"time":12376,"text":"there was a man"},{"time":14127,"text":"who traveled many miles"},{"time":15994,"text":"to come to work at the jewel in the kingdom's crown --"},{"time":19576,"text":"an internationally famous company."},{"time":22160,"text":"Let's call it Island Networks."},{"time":25278,"text":"Now this kingdom had many resources"},{"time":28126,"text":"and mighty ambitions,"},{"time":30343,"text":"but the one thing it lacked was people."},{"time":32910,"text":"And so it invited workers from around the world"},{"time":36343,"text":"to come and help it build the nation."},{"time":38993,"text":"But in order to enter and to stay"},{"time":41960,"text":"these migrants had to pass a few tests."},{"time":45495,"text":"And so it was, our man presented himself"},{"time":47978,"text":"to authorities in the kingdom,"},{"time":49747,"text":"looking forward to settling into his new life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52945,"text":"But then something unexpected happened."},{"time":56195,"text":"The medical personnel who took blood samples from the man"},{"time":59795,"text":"never actually told him what they were testing for."},{"time":63478,"text":"He wasn't offered counseling before or after the test,"},{"time":67747,"text":"which is best medical practice."},{"time":70078,"text":"He was never informed of the results of the test."},{"time":73079,"text":"And yet, a couple of weeks later,"},{"time":75195,"text":"he was picked up and taken to prison"},{"time":78229,"text":"where he was subjected to a medical exam,"},{"time":80763,"text":"including a full-body search"},{"time":83514,"text":"in full view of the others in the cell."},{"time":87112,"text":"He was released, but then a day or two later,"},{"time":90879,"text":"he was taken to the airport and he was deported."},{"time":95848,"text":"What on earth did this man do"},{"time":99113,"text":"to merit this treatment?"},{"time":101263,"text":"What was his terrible crime?"},{"time":103865,"text":"He was infected with HIV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107513,"text":"Now the kingdom is one of about 50 countries"},{"time":110644,"text":"that imposes restrictions on the entry or stay"},{"time":114916,"text":"of people living with HIV."},{"time":117516,"text":"The kingdom argues"},{"time":119117,"text":"that its laws allow it to detain or deport foreigners"},{"time":124317,"text":"who pose a risk to the economy"},{"time":127016,"text":"or the security or the public health"},{"time":130516,"text":"or the morals of the state."},{"time":132633,"text":"But these laws, when applied to people living with HIV,"},{"time":136466,"text":"are a violation of international human rights agreements"},{"time":139848,"text":"to which these countries are signatories."},{"time":143068,"text":"But you know what?"},{"time":144316,"text":"Matters of principle aside,"},{"time":145799,"text":"practically speaking, these laws drive HIV underground."},{"time":150784,"text":"People are less likely to come forth"},{"time":153382,"text":"to be tested or treated or to disclose their condition,"},{"time":157416,"text":"none of which helps these individuals"},{"time":160248,"text":"or the communities these laws purport to protect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164417,"text":"Today we can prevent the transmission of HIV."},{"time":168482,"text":"And with treatment, it is a manageable condition."},{"time":171901,"text":"We are very far from the days"},{"time":174732,"text":"when the only practical response to dread disease"},{"time":177918,"text":"was to have banished the afflicted --"},{"time":180498,"text":"like this, \"The Exile of the Leper.\""},{"time":183400,"text":"So you tell me why, in our age of science,"},{"time":186617,"text":"we still have laws and policies"},{"time":189183,"text":"which come from an age of superstition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192466,"text":"Time for a quick show of hands."},{"time":195733,"text":"Who here has been touched by HIV --"},{"time":198998,"text":"either because you yourself have the virus"},{"time":202082,"text":"or you have a family member or a friend or a colleague"},{"time":205567,"text":"who is living with HIV?"},{"time":207600,"text":"Hands up."},{"time":208700,"text":"Wow. Wow."},{"time":210681,"text":"That's a significant number of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213600,"text":"You know better than anyone"},{"time":216132,"text":"that HIV brings out"},{"time":218399,"text":"the best and the worst in humanity."},{"time":221982,"text":"And the laws reflect these attitudes."},{"time":224702,"text":"I'm not just talking about laws on the books,"},{"time":227382,"text":"but laws as they are enforced on the streets"},{"time":230749,"text":"and laws as they are decided in the courts."},{"time":233682,"text":"And I'm not just talking about laws"},{"time":236232,"text":"as they relate to people living with HIV,"},{"time":238601,"text":"but people who are at greatest risk of infection --"},{"time":241832,"text":"people such as those who inject drugs or sex workers"},{"time":245600,"text":"or men who have sex with men"},{"time":247749,"text":"or transgendered persons"},{"time":249632,"text":"or migrants or prisoners."},{"time":252100,"text":"And in many parts of the world that includes women and children"},{"time":255650,"text":"who are especially vulnerable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257681,"text":"Now there are laws in many parts of the world"},{"time":260483,"text":"which reflect the best of human nature."},{"time":263915,"text":"These laws treat people touched by HIV"},{"time":267201,"text":"with compassion and acceptance."},{"time":270100,"text":"These laws respect universal human rights"},{"time":273499,"text":"and they are grounded in evidence."},{"time":276183,"text":"These laws ensure that people living with HIV"},{"time":279316,"text":"and those at greatest risk"},{"time":281432,"text":"are protected from violence and discrimination"},{"time":285016,"text":"and that they get access to prevention and to treatment."},{"time":289232,"text":"Unfortunately, these good laws"},{"time":292028,"text":"are counter-balanced by a mass"},{"time":294164,"text":"of really bad law --"},{"time":297165,"text":"law which is grounded in moral judgement"},{"time":301614,"text":"and in fear and in misinformation,"},{"time":304467,"text":"laws which specifically punish people living with HIV"},{"time":308566,"text":"or those at greatest risk."},{"time":310198,"text":"These laws fly in the face of science,"},{"time":312965,"text":"and they are grounded in prejudice"},{"time":316248,"text":"and in ignorance and in a rewriting of tradition"},{"time":320066,"text":"and a selective reading of religion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323348,"text":"But you know what? You don't have to take my word for it."},{"time":325965,"text":"We're going to hear from two people"},{"time":327849,"text":"who are on the sharp end of the law."},{"time":330382,"text":"The first is Nick Rhoades. He's an American."},{"time":332583,"text":"And he was convicted under the U.S. State of Iowa's law"},{"time":336581,"text":"on HIV transmission and exposure --"},{"time":339466,"text":"neither of which offense he actually committed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342918,"text":"(Video) Nick Rhoades: If something is against the law"},{"time":346116,"text":"then that is telling society"},{"time":347315,"text":"that is unacceptable, that's bad behavior."},{"time":349916,"text":"And I think the severity of that punishment"},{"time":352486,"text":"tells you how bad you are as a person."},{"time":356175,"text":"You're a class B felon,"},{"time":358665,"text":"lifetime sex offender."},{"time":361449,"text":"You are a very, very, very bad person."},{"time":365482,"text":"And you did a very, very, very bad thing."},{"time":368869,"text":"And so that's just programmed into you."},{"time":371424,"text":"And you go through the correctional system"},{"time":374657,"text":"and everyone's telling you the same thing."},{"time":376458,"text":"And you're just like, I'm a very bad person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381422,"text":"Shereen El-Feki: It's not just a question"},{"time":383387,"text":"of unfair or ineffective laws."},{"time":386486,"text":"Some countries have good laws,"},{"time":388587,"text":"laws which could stem the tide of HIV."},{"time":391237,"text":"The problem is that these laws are flouted."},{"time":394337,"text":"Because stigma gives unofficial license"},{"time":397304,"text":"to treat people living with HIV"},{"time":399621,"text":"or those at greatest risk"},{"time":400937,"text":"unlike other citizens."},{"time":403271,"text":"And this is exactly what happened"},{"time":404970,"text":"to Helma and Dongo from Namibia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408184,"text":"(Video) Hilma: I found out"},{"time":409911,"text":"when I went to the hospital for a pregnancy check-up."},{"time":412856,"text":"The nurse announced that every pregnant woman"},{"time":416508,"text":"must also be tested for HIV that day."},{"time":418603,"text":"I took the test and the result showed I was positive."},{"time":421652,"text":"That's the day I found out."},{"time":424248,"text":"The nurse said to me, \"Why should you people bcome pregnant"},{"time":426860,"text":"when you know you are HIV positive?"},{"time":428388,"text":"Why are you pregnant when you are living positive?\""},{"time":430783,"text":"I am sure now that is the reason they sterilized me."},{"time":433772,"text":"Because I am HIV positive."},{"time":438904,"text":"They didn't give the forms to me"},{"time":441950,"text":"or explain what was in the form."},{"time":445672,"text":"The nurse just came with it"},{"time":448072,"text":"already marked where I had to sign."},{"time":450154,"text":"And with the labor pain,"},{"time":452098,"text":"I didn't have the strength to ask them to read it to me."},{"time":459168,"text":"I just signed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461712,"text":"SE: Hilma and Nick and our man in the kingdom"},{"time":464850,"text":"are among the 34 million people living with HIV"},{"time":469201,"text":"according to recent estimates."},{"time":471317,"text":"They're the lucky ones"},{"time":473185,"text":"because they're still alive."},{"time":474869,"text":"According to those same estimates,"},{"time":476734,"text":"in 2010 1.8 million people died"},{"time":480718,"text":"of AIDS related causes."},{"time":483117,"text":"These are terrible and tragic figures."},{"time":486620,"text":"But if we look a little more broadly into the statistics,"},{"time":491051,"text":"we actually see some reason for hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494252,"text":"Looking globally, the number of new infections of HIV is declining."},{"time":499652,"text":"And looking globally as well,"},{"time":502103,"text":"deaths are also starting to fall."},{"time":505469,"text":"There are many reasons for these positive developments,"},{"time":507502,"text":"but one of the most remarkable"},{"time":509635,"text":"is in the increase in the number of people around the world"},{"time":512802,"text":"on anti-retroviral therapy,"},{"time":514985,"text":"the medicines they need to keep their HIV in check."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519118,"text":"Now there are still many problems."},{"time":521151,"text":"Only about half of the people who need treatment"},{"time":524501,"text":"are currently receiving it."},{"time":526734,"text":"In some parts of the world --"},{"time":528586,"text":"like here in the Middle East and North Africa --"},{"time":530935,"text":"new infections are rising and so are deaths."},{"time":534318,"text":"And the money, the money we need"},{"time":537469,"text":"for the global response to HIV,"},{"time":539402,"text":"that is shrinking."},{"time":542398,"text":"But for the first time"},{"time":544687,"text":"in three decades into this epidemic"},{"time":547905,"text":"we have a real chance to come to grips with HIV."},{"time":552022,"text":"But in order to do that"},{"time":553988,"text":"we need to tackle an epidemic of really bad law."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557887,"text":"It's for this reason"},{"time":559505,"text":"that the Global Commission on HIV and the Law,"},{"time":561635,"text":"of which I'm a member,"},{"time":562934,"text":"was established by the agencies of the United Nations --"},{"time":566000,"text":"to look at the ways that legal environments"},{"time":568650,"text":"are affecting people living with HIV"},{"time":570667,"text":"and those at greatest risk,"},{"time":572801,"text":"and to recommend what should be done"},{"time":574551,"text":"to make the law an ally, not an enemy,"},{"time":577787,"text":"of the global response to HIV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580519,"text":"Let me give you just one example"},{"time":582868,"text":"of the way a legal environment"},{"time":585518,"text":"can make a positive difference."},{"time":588084,"text":"People who inject drugs"},{"time":590899,"text":"are one of those groups I mentioned."},{"time":592714,"text":"They're at high risk of HIV"},{"time":594835,"text":"through contaminated injection equipment"},{"time":596700,"text":"and other risk-related behaviors."},{"time":599382,"text":"In fact, one in every 10 new infections of HIV"},{"time":603064,"text":"is among people who inject drugs."},{"time":605798,"text":"Now drug use or possession"},{"time":608399,"text":"is illegal in almost every country."},{"time":610548,"text":"But some countries take a harder line on this than others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614798,"text":"In Thailand people who use drugs,"},{"time":617482,"text":"or are merely suspected of using drugs,"},{"time":620333,"text":"are placed in detention centers,"},{"time":622199,"text":"like the one you see here,"},{"time":624116,"text":"where they are supposed to clean up."},{"time":626199,"text":"There is absolutely no evidence"},{"time":629131,"text":"to show that throwing people into detention"},{"time":631982,"text":"cures their drug dependence."},{"time":634315,"text":"There is, however, ample evidence"},{"time":636482,"text":"to show that incarcerating people"},{"time":638482,"text":"increases their risk of HIV and other infections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643700,"text":"We know how to reduce HIV transmission and other risks"},{"time":649350,"text":"in people who inject drugs."},{"time":651115,"text":"It's called harm reduction,"},{"time":653246,"text":"and it involves, among other things,"},{"time":655030,"text":"providing clean needles and syringes,"},{"time":658161,"text":"offering opioid substitution therapy"},{"time":660996,"text":"and other evidence-based treatments"},{"time":663262,"text":"to reduce drug dependence."},{"time":665512,"text":"It involves providing information"},{"time":668029,"text":"and education and condoms"},{"time":670047,"text":"to reduce HIV transmission,"},{"time":673178,"text":"and also providing HIV testing"},{"time":675695,"text":"and counseling and treatment"},{"time":677528,"text":"should people become infected."},{"time":679346,"text":"Where the legal environment allows for harm reduction"},{"time":682879,"text":"the results are striking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685133,"text":"Australia and Switzerland"},{"time":686963,"text":"were two countries which introduced harm reduction"},{"time":689564,"text":"very early on in their HIV epidemics,"},{"time":692264,"text":"and they have a very low rate of HIV"},{"time":695283,"text":"among injecting drug users."},{"time":697446,"text":"The U.S. and Malaysia"},{"time":699797,"text":"came to harm reduction a little later,"},{"time":702347,"text":"and they have higher rates of HIV in these populations."},{"time":706314,"text":"Thailand and Russia, however,"},{"time":707997,"text":"have resisted harm reduction"},{"time":709899,"text":"and have stringent laws"},{"time":711631,"text":"which punish drug use."},{"time":713197,"text":"And hey, surprise,"},{"time":714697,"text":"very high rates of HIV among people who are injecting drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720064,"text":"At the Global Commission we have studied the evidence,"},{"time":722930,"text":"and we've heard the experiences"},{"time":724681,"text":"of over 700 people from 140 countries."},{"time":729014,"text":"And the trend? Well the trend is clear."},{"time":731272,"text":"Where you criminalize people living with HIV"},{"time":734597,"text":"or those at greatest risk,"},{"time":735963,"text":"you fuel the epidemic."},{"time":738712,"text":"Now coming up with a vaccine for HIV"},{"time":742981,"text":"or a cure for AIDS --"},{"time":744182,"text":"now that's rocket science."},{"time":746680,"text":"But changing the law isn't."},{"time":748463,"text":"And in fact, a number of countries are starting to make progress"},{"time":751176,"text":"on a number of points."},{"time":752759,"text":"To begin, countries need to review their legislation"},{"time":756797,"text":"as it touches HIV and vulnerable groups."},{"time":760329,"text":"On the back of those reviews,"},{"time":762446,"text":"governments should repeal laws"},{"time":764412,"text":"that punish or discriminate against people living with HIV"},{"time":767580,"text":"or those at greatest risk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769797,"text":"Repealing a law isn't easy,"},{"time":772313,"text":"and it's particularly difficult"},{"time":774097,"text":"when it relates to touchy subjects like drugs and sex."},{"time":778380,"text":"But there's plenty you can do while that process is underway."},{"time":781947,"text":"One of the key points is to reform the police"},{"time":786246,"text":"so that they have better practices on the ground."},{"time":789063,"text":"So for example, outreach workers"},{"time":790818,"text":"who are distributing condoms to vulnerable populations"},{"time":793818,"text":"are not themselves subject to police harassment"},{"time":796934,"text":"or abuse or arbitrary arrest."},{"time":799884,"text":"We can also train judges"},{"time":801385,"text":"so that they find flexibilities in the law"},{"time":804552,"text":"and so that they rule on the side of tolerance"},{"time":807702,"text":"rather than prejudice."},{"time":809601,"text":"We can retool prisons"},{"time":811119,"text":"so that HIV prevention and harm reduction"},{"time":814484,"text":"is available to prisoners."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816704,"text":"The key to all this is reinforcing civil society."},{"time":821219,"text":"Because civil society is key"},{"time":822902,"text":"to raising awareness among vulnerable groups"},{"time":825768,"text":"of their legal rights."},{"time":827552,"text":"But awareness needs action."},{"time":829169,"text":"And so we need to ensure"},{"time":830635,"text":"that these people who are living with HIV"},{"time":832968,"text":"or at greatest risk of HIV"},{"time":834635,"text":"have access to legal services"},{"time":837369,"text":"and they have equal access to the courts."},{"time":840285,"text":"And also important is talking to communities"},{"time":842986,"text":"so that we change interpretations"},{"time":845135,"text":"of religious or customary law,"},{"time":847635,"text":"which is too often used"},{"time":849453,"text":"to justify punishment and fuel stigma."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852936,"text":"For many of us here"},{"time":854184,"text":"HIV is not an abstract threat."},{"time":857703,"text":"It hits very close to home."},{"time":860202,"text":"The law, on the other hand,"},{"time":862719,"text":"can seem remote, arcane, the stuff of specialists,"},{"time":867152,"text":"but it isn't."},{"time":869234,"text":"Because for those of us who live in democracies,"},{"time":872119,"text":"or in aspiring democracies,"},{"time":874435,"text":"the law begins with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877452,"text":"Laws that treat people living with HIV"},{"time":880385,"text":"or those at greatest risk with respect"},{"time":883053,"text":"start with the way that we treat them ourselves: as equals."},{"time":887901,"text":"If we are going to stop the spread of HIV in our lifetime,"},{"time":892535,"text":"then that is the change we need to spread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896202,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897601,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}